240 grams British Beef Mince
40 grams Mature Cheddar Cheese
2 unit(s) Burger Buns
10 grams Beef Stock Paste
45 grams Burger Sauce
20 grams Baby Leaf Mix
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
15 milliliter(s) Cider Vinegar
1 sachet(s) Crispy Onions
2 tbsp Tomato Ketchup
50 milliliter(s) Water
1 tbsp Olive Oil
½ tsp Sugar

Heat a frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the beef mince, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the cheese.
Halve the burger buns.
Toast the buns in your toaster.

Once the beef has browned, stir in the beef stock paste, ketchup and water (see pantry for both).
Simmer, 1-2 mins. Add a splash of water if needed.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, mix together the baby leaves, coleslaw mix, cider vinegar and the oil and sugar (see pantry for both). Toss to coat.

Lay the toasted buns on plates, cut-side up.
Top with the beef mince, cheese and burger sauce - as much as you'd like.
Sprinkle the crispy onions over.
Serve the salad on the side.
Enjoy!